cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on transferring grasping skills for robotic manipulation. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper uses non-rigid registration methods to establish correspondences between shapes. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper proposes a new approach for accumulating grasping knowledge into a category-level canonical model. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses subspace methods to improve the non-rigid registration. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with geometric deformations and shape correspondences.
